Overall, we use three types of examination functions (linear, discounted, and inverse), which assume that item exposure diminishes with decreasing ranking either linearly, or with an increasing penalty that is either proportional to the rank decrease or the inverse of the rank. Generally, the most punishing is the inverse function, and the least punishing is the DCG-based discount function. (Saito2022FairRanking).
